General Instructions
1.  The user starts the Anteater Chess program through the terminal interface.
2a. Upon launching the program, select to play against a bot or against a friend. 
2b. If playing against a bot select a side (white or black).
3.  Inputs moves using coordinate notation (e.g., F2 F4).
4a. After each move the system validates the input and updates the board.
4b. If playing against a bot The computer generates and executes its move.
5.  Checkmate the opposing King to Win!


